      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to physical test article and test setup within stated uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "CMM-measured geometry used in FEA matches test articles within 0.05 mm. Test machine fixture compliance characterized and incorporated as boundary condition spring element. Material properties from same production lot as test articles."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) < 1.96 and percent difference < 10% for all three QoIs; comparison accounts for experimental uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "E/uval values: stiffness 0.87, yield force 1.21, 40 mm force 1.09. Percent differences: stiffness 3.2%, yield force 6.8%, 40 mm force 4.5%. All three QoIs satisfy both acceptance criteria. Experimental uncertainty estimated from inter-lab and intra-lab variability."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
