      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness relates to load sharing with bone graft; yield force predicts onset of permanent deformation leading to loss of correction; force at 40 mm displacement is ASTM F1717 regulatory benchmark. All three QoIs directly relevant to COU."
